label: organic matter
definition: A chemical compound that contain carbon-hydrogen or carbon-carbon bonds.
editors note: Root is chemistry compound upper level term. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organic_compound

label: inorganic matter
definition: A chemical compound that lacks carbon–hydrogen bonds and is therefore not an organic compound.
comment: There are a few notable exception e.g., carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide, carbides, as well as various salts.
editors note: Root is chemistry compound upper level term.  See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inorganic_compound

label: dissolved organic carbon
definition: The carbon compound fraction of dissolved organic matter.

label: dissolved inorganic carbon
definition: The carbon compound fraction of dissolved inorganic matter.

label: dissolved organic nitrogen
definition: The nitrogen compound fraction of dissolved organic matter.
editors note: Dissolved organic nitrogen (DON) is that subset of the dissolved organic carbon (DOC) pool that also contains N.

label: dissolved inorganic nitrogen
definition: The nitrogen compound fraction of dissolved inorganic matter.

label: dissolved organic phosphorus
definition: The phosphorus compound fraction of dissolved organic matter.

label: dissolved inorganic phosphorus
definition: The phosphorus compound fraction of dissolved inorganic matter.

label: particulate organic matter
comment: A fraction of total organic matter operationally defined as that which does not pass through a filter pore size that typically ranges in size from 0.053 to 2 millimeters.

label: particulate organic carbon
definition: The carbon compound fraction of particulate organic matter.
comment: The mass of carbon in the particulate organic material

label: particulate inorganic carbon
definition: The carbon compound fraction of particulate inorganic matter.

label: particulate organic nitrogen
definition: The nitrogen compound fraction of particulate organic matter.

label: particulate inorganic nitrogen
definition: The nitrogen compound fraction of particulate inorganic matter.

label: particulate organic phosphorus
definition: The phosphorus compound fraction of particulate organic matter.

label: particulate inorganic phosphorus
definition: The phosphorus compound fraction of particulate inorganic matter.
